{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"PLAN-REVIEW TRIAGE (verdict PASS; 10 advisories). Accepted, to fold into ACs at implementation: (1) make the tuning thresholds CONFIGURABLE and state defaults — free-space watermark %, mtime grace window, max-age cutoff, integrity-reverify period; (2) add covering ACs for the max-age cold trim, the startup sweep (rmtree tmp/*,trash/*), and the incrementally-maintained byte total; (3) byte-total updates must be atomic/owned so concurrent lock-free populate vs under-gc/lock evict cannot drift (TOCTOU); (4) define trash straggler ownership if the janitor crashes after rename-to-trash but before rmtree, between startup sweeps; (5) write an ADR capturing the delete-on-last-close + flock-interlock + content-addressed-layout design AND the rejected PID+heartbeat lease (spike outcome). None judged invalid."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782522695501814001,"uuid":"4b6c0487-5d1e-4ef9-b25b-2925da1b2d5f"}